The paper deals with coded caching schemes for combination networks, which involve the use of coding techniques to reduce the amount of data transmitted in a network. This is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Given the focus on information theory and networking, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of coding techniques and the focus on optimization suggest that cs.SI, cs.DC, and cs.CC are also possible sub-categories.
